args:
When the prince and his allies finally reach the
throne room, the Other demands the Prince give
up his own body in exchange for saving Zethia.
The prince agrees, but before the transfer can
be completed, Beren shows up and initiates a
surprise attack against the Other.
We're here. Morsayati and Zethia\nare waiting for us just inside.
Dude, I can't believe we're\nFINALLY gonna save Zethia!
You're damn right we are, Notte.\nCome on, everyone.

You have done well to come this far, little
prince. As the Holywyrm's chosen holder
of countless pacts, I expected no less.
I have been awaiting you most eagerly.
This ends today, Morsayati!\nI'm freeing Zethia!
Well, depending on your attitude,\nperhaps we COULD arrange to\nhave this body returned to her.
I trust this dude about as far as I can\nthrow him—and these little stick arms\ncan't throw ANYTHING!
In a way, Prince, your sister is my home.\nAnd when a person purchases a fine new\nhome, they have no need for the old one.

So if there was a vessel more suited to
housing my soul—perhaps one that held
free control over dragons—I would not be
particular about holding onto the Auspex.
Okay, hang on. You think we're all gonna\njust stand around and let you possess\n{player_name}?! No way, fool!
I will not permit you to lay one slimy\nfinger upon my darling!

The method of my seizing control is of
no consequence. We can do it peacefully
and let all of you live, or I can slaughter
you and claim the prince's body after.
Though I cannot say for certain that the\nAuspex's body is strong enough to\nsurvive such an ordeal...

Oh, that is EXACTLY what I'm saying.
I've been using and abusing this body
over the months, you see, and I fear it
cannot endure the strain much longer.
But if you willingly surrender yourself as\nmy vessel, I no longer need the Auspex\nand will return her to you unharmed.
So then, little prince! What is your course?\nWill you lay down your life for your sister,\nor sacrifice her in the name of ＂peace＂?
Have you lost the last damn marble\nrollin' around yer head, boss?!
Your Highness, you cannot do this thing!\nIf you were gone, who would bring peace\nto all Alberia?!
Are you not the one who has taken up\nthe dying wish of King Alberius?!
I'm sorry—and I know this looks like I'm\nbetraying everyone who trusted me...
But it's the only way to save Zethia.
You promised the three of us would be\ntogether again! You PROMISED!
I'm sorry, Notte. I'm...I'm so sorry.
Heh. It seems you've resolved yourself.\nWell, then—let us begin the rite\nof transference.
No! I won't let this happen!
I'm right there with ya, my man.\nWe're gonna wait for the right moment\nand put a stop to all'a this crap!

A word of warning to the rest of you:
If the rite is interrupted, the body of the
chosen vessel might... Well, let us just
say it would be VERY messy.
So I suggest you just sit there like good\nlittle humans, unless you wish to see\nyour dear friend turned inside out.
Ya mean I gotta wait here like a chump\nand just watch him get possessed?!\nGraaaaagh! Dammit all to hell!
AAAAH HA HA HA HA! The time grows\nnigh for that loathsome Elysium's—
You're... Why have you come here now?
It's the kid! The fifth scion!
The hell is he doing here?!
You there. Fiend of fiends.\nYou will become one with me.
Idiot child! Do you think I, the great\nMorsayati, would be caught unawares\nby such a weak and obvious power?
You are fools who forget your place,\nand now I will show you how to wield\nblack mana for true! Haaaaah!
It is you who has forgotten his place.
...What? Wait, no. Wh-what is this?\nWho are you?! WHO THE DEVIL ARE YOU?!
Struggling is useless—you are\nfated to meet your end here.\n...One you know well said as much.
How can you be this strong?!\nRETURN MY POWER!\nRETURN IT TO MEEEEEEEE!
